headlines.description: — LaMelo Ball scored 17 of his 31 points in the fourth quarter, Brandon Miller tied a career high with seven 3-pointers and had 29 points and the Charlotte Hornets overcame a 13-point deficit to beat the Indiana Pacers 103-83 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ball scores 31 points, Miller has 29 to help the Hornets beat the Pacers, 103-83

headlines.description: — Cade Cunningham finished his third consecutive triple-double by scoring the winning basket with 8.5 seconds left, and the Detroit Pistons beat the Atlanta Hawks 122-121 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cunningham finishes triple-double with huge plays at both ends as Pistons beat Hawks 122-121

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Orlando Magic

headlines.description: — Franz Wagner scored 27 points and the Orlando Magic broke a five-game losing streak, never trailing in a 115-88 victory over the injury-depleted New Orleans Pelicans on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Magic snap 5-game losing streak, beating injury-depleted Pelicans 115-88

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Cleveland Cavaliers

headlines.description: — Darius Garland scored 27 points and Evan Mobley had 23 as the Cleveland Cavaliers routed the Golden State Warriors 136-117 on Friday night, extending their <a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Cavaliers take 41-point halftime lead and rout Warriors 136-117 to improve to 10-0

events.name: Milwaukee Bucks at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns had 32 points, 11 rebounds and five assists and the New York Knicks snapped a two-game losing streak with a 116-94 win over the Milwaukee Bucks on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns scores 32 in Knicks' 116-94 win over struggling Bucks

headlines.description: — Jusuf Nurkic made the second of two free throws with 0.8 seconds left after getting fouled on an offensive rebound, lifting the Phoenix Suns to a 114-113 victory over the Dallas Mavericks on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jusuf Nurkic makes free throw with 0.8 seconds left to lift Suns past Mavs, 114-113

headlines.description: — Jaren Jackson Jr. scored 39 points, Scotty Pippen Jr. got his first career triple-double and Memphis Grizzlies beat the Washington Wizards 128-104 on Friday night for their fourth win in five games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jackson scores 39 points, Pippen has triple-double as Grizzlies beat Wizards 128-104

events.name: Houston Rockets at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander and Chet Holmgren each scored 29 points to help the Oklahoma City Thunder rout the Houston Rockets 126-107 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander and Holmgren each score 29 points, Thunder rout Rockets 126-107

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards hit nine 3-pointers and scored 37 points to help the Minnesota Timberwolves beat the Portland Trail Blazers 127-102 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards hits 9 3-pointers as Timberwolves blow out Trail Blazers 127-102

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 30 points, 14 assists and 11 rebounds for his third straight triple-double to lead the Denver Nuggets past the Miami Heat 135-122 Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nikola Jokic's third straight triple-double leads Nuggets past Heat 135-122

headlines.description: — LeBron James had 21 points, 13 assists and 12 rebounds in his second triple-double of the season, and the Los Angeles Lakers extended the Philadelphia 76ers' miserable start with a 116-106...
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron has his 114th triple-double in the Lakers' 116-106 win over the slumping 76ers

headlines.description: — Norman Powell posted his first career double-double with 31 points and 12 rebounds, and the Los Angeles Clippers beat the Sacramento Kings 107-98 on Friday night for their third straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Norman Powell has 31 points and 12 rebounds as the Clippers hold off the Kings 107-98
